      "$description": "Fog — Muted body text, helper annotations"
    },
    "pure-white": {
      "$value": "#ffffff",
      "$type": "color",
      "$description": "Pure White — Light supporting surface for subtle backgrounds and section separation. Do not promote it to the primary CTA color"
    },
    "amber-whisper": {
      "$value": "#e7c59a",
      "$type": "color",
      "$description": "Amber Whisper — Sole chromatic accent — availability badge highlight, subtle brand warmth, the single chromatic note in an otherwise achromatic system"
    }
  },
  "font": {
    "aeonik": {
      "$value": "Aeonik",
      "$type": "fontFamily",
      "$description": "Primary typeface for all interface text — body, headings, nav, buttons, CTAs. The 700 weight is used sparingly for uppercase section labels (SERVICES, PORTFOLIO, PROCESS, READ MANIFESTO) creating a stencil-like rhythm against the 400-weight body and light display headings."
    },
    "input": {
      "$value": "Input",
      "$type": "fontFamily",
      "$description": "Mono-adjacent secondary face for micro-labels, metadata, technical annotations, and the smallest badge text. Its dramatically tighter tracking (−0.037em, −0.022em) makes it read as 'system text' — distinct from Aeonik's editorial warmth. Use for timestamps, version tags, and status indicators."
    }
  },
